  "text": "The Kubernetes Deployment to Pod creation chain flows through multiple controllers and API layers:\n\n1. DEPLOYMENT CONTROLLER RECONCILIATION:\n   File: pkg/controller/deployment/deployment_controller.go\n   Symbol: DeploymentController.syncDeployment (line 590)\n   \n   When a Deployment spec changes, the Deployment controller's syncDeployment function is triggered. It lists ReplicaSets, gets pods, and invokes the appropriate strategy (rolling or recreate).\n\n2. REPLICASET CREATION:\n   File: pkg/controller/deployment/sync.go\n   Symbol: DeploymentController.getNewReplicaSet (line 138)\n   \n   The Deployment controller creates a new ReplicaSet via the API at line 224:\n   `createdRS, err := dc.client.AppsV1().ReplicaSets(d.Namespace).Create(ctx, &newRS, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n   \n   This ReplicaSet is created with proper ownership references and pod template specifications.\n\n3. REPLICASET CONTROLLER RECONCILIATION:\n   File: pkg/controller/replicaset/replica_set.go\n   Symbol: ReplicaSetController.syncReplicaSet (line 675)\n   \n   When the ReplicaSet is created, the ReplicaSet controller watches it via an informer and triggers syncReplicaSet. This function reconciles the desired pod count by calling manageReplicas.\n\n4. POD MANAGEMENT:\n   File: pkg/controller/replicaset/replica_set.go\n   Symbol: ReplicaSetController.manageReplicas (line 569)\n   \n   The manageReplicas function determines how many pods need to be created or deleted. It calls slowStartBatch to create pods in batches, invoking:\n   `rsc.podControl.CreatePods(ctx, rs.Namespace, &rs.Spec.Template, rs, metav1.NewControllerRef(rs, rsc.GroupVersionKind))` at line 598\n\n5. POD CREATION VIA API:\n   File: pkg/controller/controller_utils.go\n   Symbol: RealPodControl.createPods (line 578)\n   \n   The pod control implementation creates pods via the Kubernetes API at line 582:\n   `newPod, err := r.KubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Create(ctx, pod, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n   \n   This delegates to the API server.\n\n6. API SERVER POD STORAGE:\n   File: pkg/registry/core/pod/storage/storage.go\n   Symbol: NewStorage (line 72)\n   \n   The API server's Pod storage layer uses a genericregistry.Store with the pod strategy for handling creates. The store is configured with CreateStrategy: registrypod.Strategy.\n\n7. POD CREATION STRATEGY:\n   File: pkg/registry/core/pod/strategy.go\n   Symbol: podStrategy.PrepareForCreate (line 86)\n   \n   When a Pod Create request arrives at the API server, the podStrategy.PrepareForCreate function is called. It initializes the pod status to Pending and applies QoS classes and field mutations. The pod is then validated and stored in etcd.\n\nThe complete chain: Deployment spec change → Deployment controller creates ReplicaSet → ReplicaSet controller watches ReplicaSet → ReplicaSet controller creates Pods via PodControl → PodControl calls API server → API server's Pod storage creates Pod in etcd."
